data.title: Indonesian Occupation East Timor by Taylor John
data.meta_description: The Indonesian occupation of East Timor 1974-1989: A chronology by Taylor, John G and a great selection of related books, art and collectibles available now at AbeBooks.com.
data.text:
Condition: Good. Dirty/ripped dust cover. Your purchase helps support Sri Lankan Children's Charity 'The Rainbow Centre'. Ex-library, so some stamps and wear, but in good overall condition. Our donations to The Rainbow Centre have helped provide an education and a safe haven to hundreds of children who live in appalling conditions.

Hardcover. Condition: Very Good. Dust Jacket Condition: Very Good. First Edition. the top edge of the pages show signs of dust marks, there is no other damage to describe. The book is free of annotation. The chronology catalogues are remarkable story of resistance. Against all expectations by Indonesia and the West, the people of East Timor have refused to accept integration by force and continue to demand their rights as a people.
